<p><a name="Articles_on_his_disappearance" id="Articles_on_his_disappearance"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Ram_Bahadur_Bomjon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Articles on his disappearance">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Articles on his disappearance</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.thehimalayantimes.com/fullstory.asp?filename=6a8Wa8ta.9amal&amp;folder=aHaoamW&amp;Name=Home&amp;dtSiteDate=20061225" class="external text" title="http://www.thehimalayantimes.com/fullstory.asp?filename=6a8Wa8ta.9amal&amp;folder=aHaoamW&amp;Name=Home&amp;dtSiteDate=20061225" rel="nofollow">Missing 'Teen Buddha' Comes Back Armed</a> - (<a href="http://www.thehimalayantimes.com" class="external text" title="http://www.thehimalayantimes.com" rel="nofollow">The Himalayan Times</a>) Monday, December 25, 2006</li>
<li><a href="http://www.kantipuronline.com/kolnews.php?&amp;nid=67938" class="external text" title="http://www.kantipuronline.com/kolnews.php?&amp;nid=67938" rel="nofollow"><i>Buddha Boy</i> disappears</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cnn.com/2006/WORLD/asiapcf/03/11/nepal.missing.ap/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.cnn.com/2006/WORLD/asiapcf/03/11/nepal.missing.ap/index.html" rel="nofollow">Jungle search for teenage 'Buddha'</a> (<a href="/wiki/CNN" title="CNN">CNN</a>/<a href="/wiki/Associated_Press" title="Associated Press">Associated Press</a>) Saturday, March 11, 2006; Posted: 11:31 p.m. EST (04:31 GMT)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml?xml=/news/2006/03/13/wbomjon13.xml&amp;sSheet=/portal/2006/03/13/ixportal.html" class="external text" title="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml?xml=/news/2006/03/13/wbomjon13.xml&amp;sSheet=/portal/2006/03/13/ixportal.html" rel="nofollow">Nepal's pilgrims pray for return of 'Buddha boy'</a> report of 'sighting'; 'Guru Mother's prediction</li>
<li><a href="http://www.metimes.com/articles/normal.php?StoryID=20060314-071326-8817r" class="external text" title="http://www.metimes.com/articles/normal.php?StoryID=20060314-071326-8817r" rel="nofollow">Prayers for Nepal's missing 'Buddha Boy'</a> Nothing new but well-written</li>
<li><a href="http://news.yahoo.com/s/nm/20061225/od_uk_nm/oukoe_uk_nepal_boy" class="external autonumber" title="http://news.yahoo.com/s/nm/20061225/od_uk_nm/oukoe_uk_nepal_boy" rel="nofollow">[2]</a> Boy returns</li>
<li><a href="http://www.gulf-times.com/site/topics/article.asp?cu_no=2&amp;item_no=76941&amp;version=1&amp;template_id=44&amp;parent_id=24" class="external text" title="http://www.gulf-times.com/site/topics/article.asp?cu_no=2&amp;item_no=76941&amp;version=1&amp;template_id=44&amp;parent_id=24" rel="nofollow">Same as previous story but with new picture of troops in the compound</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.dailyindia.com/show/9624.php/Devotees_claim_Nepals_missing_Buddha_Boy_found" class="external text" title="http://www.dailyindia.com/show/9624.php/Devotees_claim_Nepals_missing_Buddha_Boy_found" rel="nofollow">Devotees claim Nepal's missing Buddha Boy found</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.nepalnews.com/archive/2006/mar/mar20/news02.php" class="external text" title="http://www.nepalnews.com/archive/2006/mar/mar20/news02.php" rel="nofollow">A few more details of his rediscovery</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=5435806" class="external text" title="http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=5435806" rel="nofollow">NPR interview with GQ writer</a> The writer went to observe Bomjon and was deeply affected</li>
</ul>


